The order and places of the oath will be determined by the President
Where and how the new Russian citizens will swear allegiance to the Russian Federation will be determined by the President - such amendments to the second reading of the relevant law was developed by the state Duma Committee on legislation and state construction.
A week ago, the deputies planned to directly determine the order of the oath in the law.
From the solemn oath will be released children under 18 years, as well as incapacitated, follows from the revised text of amendments to the bill "on citizenship of the Russian Federation" (there is at the disposal of "News"), which the Committee will consider July 11 before the second reading at its meeting.
The idea of the introduction of the oath of citizenship of the Russian Federation is the formal signing of documents, President Vladimir Putin supported a June 6 meeting with the speaker of the state Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
Deputies issued this idea in the form of amendments to the second reading in the bill providing for the abolition of the decision to grant citizenship to those who were subsequently convicted of a number of crimes of a terrorist or extremist nature: for example, for public calls for terrorism or its public justification in the media or on the Internet (part 2 of article 205.2 of the criminal code), as well as for the hijacking of an airplane, train or water transport, but only if this act is related to terrorism (part 4 of article 211 of the criminal code).
According to the draft law, the logic was as follows: when preparing documents for citizenship, a person signs a promise to comply with Russian legislation - getting on the path of extremism, he violates this promise.
The bill in April was submitted to the state Duma by the leaders of the Duma factions Vladimir Vasiliev ("United Russia"), Gennady Zyuganov (Communist party), Vladimir Zhirinovsky (LDPR), Sergei Mironov ("Fair Russia") and the speaker of the state Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
On may 19, the deputies adopted it in the first reading.
Last week, the state construction and legislation Committee of the state Duma approved the text of the draft law for the second reading, but now it has been revised once again.
Now it says that the order of oath will be established by the President of the Russian Federation.
Previously, the parliamentarians were going to describe the procedure directly in the law "on citizenship of the Russian Federation", stating that the ceremony should be held in a solemn atmosphere in front of the state emblem and flag of Russia in the presence of the representative of the interior Ministry.
However, it was not clear from the text of the draft law where such an event should take place - the list of places where the placement of the emblem of the Russian Federation is possible is regulated by the relevant Federal constitutional law.
These include courts, offices of heads of state bodies of subjects, municipalities, judges, prosecutors, heads of Federal Executive bodies, etc.
Most likely, it could be registry Offices.
Those who wish to obtain Russian citizenship will take a solemn oath after officials check their documents.
But a person will receive a Russian passport only after he takes the oath, it follows from the revised text.
A week ago, the draft stated that the oath must precede the signing of the decree.
The updated text States that Russia will be sworn in from 18 years, not 14.
The rule remains that incapacitated or partially capable persons, as well as those who cannot pronounce, read or sign the oath text themselves, will be released from taking the oath.
In addition, the Russian President has the right to release from this procedure and "other persons",
Also in the updated bill the special order of reception in the Russian citizens of Ukraine who are considered native speakers of Russian is registered.
They will have to officially renounce their Ukrainian citizenship by submitting an appropriate application to the authorized body of Ukraine.
A notarized copy of the application will need to be handed over to Russian officials.
Renunciation of" foreign "citizenship, as now, is not required if it is provided by an international Treaty or if it is impossible"for reasons beyond the control of the person."
The corresponding amendment to the law was proposed by a group of deputies, including the first Vice-speaker of the state Duma Ivan Melnikov (Communist party), Natalia Poklonskaya, Pavel Krasheninnikov and Airat Farrakhov (all - "United Russia").
I think many of you know that it is impossible to get a certificate from Ukraine, it is simply impossible.
Accordingly, a lot of people are waiting for the decision of their fate about the citizenship of the Russian Federation, - explained the head of the Duma Committee on state construction and legislation Pavel Krasheninnikov (ER).
In addition, the text added a clarification that restrictions on the employment of certain positions for foreigners will not apply to those who refused in writing to "other" citizenship and handed over the former passport to the Ministry of internal Affairs of Russia, but "for reasons beyond its control" it has not ceased to be considered a citizen of another country.
Now foreigners are forbidden to hold positions in the municipal service, to be employed at facilities and organizations whose activities are related to the security of Russia.
Also, a person with dual citizenship or residence permit of another country can not become a member of the state Duma or the Federation Council.
It is planned that the law should enter into force on September 1, 2017, by the time the necessary by-laws should be ready.
