The appearance of similarities: the artist creates portraits using DNA Chelsea manning
In the center of the hall in the Friedman Gallery in new York from the ceiling on the wire hanging faces of people-white, black and brown, all something elusive similar to each other.
These 30 portraits were created by the artist Heather Dewey Harborg from the cheek swabs and scraps of hair sent to her by Chelsea manning.
Manning sent over the clippings from Fort Levenworth prison, where a former intelligence analyst is serving a 35-year sentence for the famous transmission of confidential diplomatic telegrams on WikiLeaks.
