In Russia there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
Relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activities of the Torah in the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime of business activity, as well as the minimum amount of capital investments of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which the TOR "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of business activities, for example, includes crop production, livestock, food, soft drinks and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise "Abakan mine".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of economic development for the creation of TOP.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, a territory of advanced social and economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the single-industry city, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of JSC "Ural steel", as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investment in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOP will operate a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk was the first of the single-industry towns of the Orenburg region to receive the status of TOP.
We remind that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for the residents of the TOP, the following can be distinguished: profit tax at a rate of no more than 5% for the first five years, and no less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions at a rate of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, a preferential regime for connecting to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rental rates.
